Jordanâ€™s National Electric Power Co.
plans to boost its capital by 32 percent to 100 million dinars
($141 million), Petra reported.  Nepco, as the state company is known, will propose the
capital increase at an extraordinary general assembly meeting on
Nov. 20, the state-run news agency reported. There were no
further details on the reason behind the decision or how the new
capital will be raised.  The company incurred losses of 4.5 million dinars in the
first half of this year and 3 million dinars in the same period
of 2013, according to Petra.  To contact the reporter on this story:
